Germany has postponed the launch of a new warship.
The latest frigate of the German fleet was to be commissioned in 2014 to replace the Cold War-era obsolete warships, but this will not happen until at least next year due to faulty systems and booming costs, local media reported.
The commissioning of the Rheinland-Pfalz, the flagship of the brand’s new Baden-Wuerttemberg class frigates, has been postponed until the first half of 2019, according to the newspaper Die Zeit, which quoted an army spokesman as saying.
