"Today, the situation on the ground is more stable and safe, thanks to the progress we have made in the fight against terrorism," he said.
The government continues to rebuild areas devastated by terrorists to bring them back to normal.
Now there are all conditions for the voluntary return of refugees to the country they were forced to leave due to terrorism and unilateral economic measures that affected their daily lives and livelihoods.
The United Nations estimates that more than 5.5 million Syrians have left the country since the start of the war in 2011.
